As one of Siemens’ strategic goals, the digital transformation will only succeed if Siemens can be certain that connected systems and the data contained within them will remain secure. That is why Siemens places the highest priority on cybersecurity.

Siemens’ products, solutions, and services contain a signifi- cant amount of software and IT-related components and are often used in the context of critical infrastructures – which

Having recognized early on that cybersecurity is an integral part of the digital revolution, Siemens built a cybersecurity organization both at the corporate level and in the busi- nesses and countries. All information security rules and regulations at Siemens are documented and detailed in the Cybersecurity Policy Framework. The framework outlines the roles and responsibilities and the rules and practices that offer a guide for how Siemens and its business units protect information and business processes.